#v(0.8em)

#hm-note[
  Month 7 opens Quarter III — Inner Fire. The student moves from the high-heat
  calcination of Quarter II to the slow, steady fire of willed attention. The
  Nature Vigil is a foundational practice of the Western Alchemical tradition. It
  demands extreme patience and a reorientation of the mind toward receptivity.
  Students who struggle with the "doing nothing" aspect of the vigil often find
  their laboratory work also becomes mechanical; ensure they understand that
  witnessing is an *active* and *demanding* discipline.
]

